Almost instantly this picture faded, and a new one grew out of the confused images that remained. The form of Jenny became distinct once more, but her attitude and countenance were changed. She stood erect, with a cold, unloving face, and looked into his eyes with angry defiance, and at the same time out of his memory into his thoughts came these words:
"A woman moved is like a fountain troubled;
Dark, unseemly, thick, bereft of beauty."
